  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=Closing the Doors of the Senses
---
That man who, having heard and touched, seen and eaten and smelled, neither
rejoices nor ever is sad, he is to be known (as a man) who has conquered his
senses.

But among all the senses, if one sense fails, by that his wisdom fails, as
water (runs out) by one hole from a leather bag.
